record_data.record_plain_text: 1. Availability. Seller will make wholesale electric energy, capacity, and ancillary services available under this Tariff to any purchaser, except as prohibited below. 2. Applicability. This Tariff is applicable to all sales of energy, capacity, and ancillary services by Seller not otherwise subject to a particular rate schedule of Seller. 3. Rates. All sales shall be made at the rates established between the purchaser and Seller. 4. Other Terms and Conditions. All other terms and conditions shall be established by agreement between the purchaser and Seller. 5. Compliance with Commission Regulations. Seller shall comply with the provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, as applicable, and with any conditions the Commission imposes in its orders concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, including orders in which the Commission authorizes Seller to engage in affiliate sales under this Tariff or otherwise restricts or limits the Seller’s market-based rate authority. Failure to comply with the applicable provisions of 18 C.F.R. Part 35, Subpart H, and with any orders of the Commission concerning Seller’s market-based rate authority, will constitute a violation of this Tariff. 6. Limitations and Exemptions Regarding Market Based Rate Authority. Seller does not have any limitations on its market-based rate authority except as otherwise provided in this Tariff. The Commission granted Seller in Docket No. ER23-___-000 the following waivers and blanket authorization: (a) waiver of Subparts B and C of Part 35 of the Commission’s regulations requiring the filing of cost-of-service information, except for sections 35.12(a), 35.13(b), 35.15 and 35.16; (b) waiver of the requirements of Part 41 and Part 101, with the exception that waiver of the provisions of Part 101 that apply to hydropower licensees is not granted with respect to licensed hydropower projects; (c) waiver of Part 141 of the Commission’s regulations concerning accounting and reporting requirements, with the exception of 18 C.F.R. §§ 141.14 and 141.15; and (d) blanket approval as to Section 204 of the FPA and Part 34 of the Commission’s regulations for all future issuances of securities and debt and assumption of liabilities. 7. Ancillary Services. PJM: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, energy imbalance service, and operating reserve service (which includes spinning, 10-minute, and 30-minute reserves) for sale into the market administered by PJM Interconnection, L.L.C. (“PJM”) and, where the PJM Open Access Transmission Tariff permits, the self-supply of these services to purchasers for a bilateral sale that is used to satisfy the ancillary services requirements of the PJM Office of Interconnection. New York: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service, and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute non-synchronous, 30-minute operating reserves, 10-minute spinning reserves, and 10-minute non-spinning reserves) for sale to purchasers in the market administered by the New York Independent System Operator, Inc. New England: Seller offers regulation and frequency response service (automatic generator control), operating reserve service (which includes 10-minute spinning reserve, 10-minute non-spinning reserve, and 30-minute operating reserve service) to purchasers within the markets administered by the ISO New England, Inc. California: Seller offers regulation service, spinning reserve service, and non-spinning reserve service to the California Independent System Operator Corporation (“CAISO”) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to the CAISO. MISO: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. (MISO) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to MISO. Southwest Power Pool: Seller offers regulation service and operating reserve service (which include 10-minute spinning reserve and 10-minute supplemental reserve) for sale to the Southwest Power Pool, Inc. (SPP) and to others that are self-supplying ancillary services to SPP. Third-party ancillary services: Seller offers Regulation Service, Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service, Energy and Generator Imbalance Service, Operating Reserve-Spinning, Operating Reserve-Supplemental, and Primary Frequency Response Service. Sales will not include the following: (1) sales to an RTO or an ISO, i.e., where that entity has no ability to self-supply ancillary services but instead depends on third parties; and (2) sales to a traditional, franchised public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier, or sales where the underlying transmission service is on the system of the public utility affiliated with the third-party supplier. Sales of Operating Reserve-Spinning and Operating Reserve-Supplemental will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except where the Commission has granted authorization. Sales of Regulation Service and Reactive Supply and Voltage Control Service will not include sales to a public utility that is purchasing ancillary services to satisfy its own open access transmission tariff requirements to offer ancillary services to its own customers, except at rates not to exceed the buying public utility transmission provider’s OATT rate for the same service or where the Commission has granted authorization. 8. Seller Category. Seller is a Category 2 Seller in the Southwest region and a Category 1 Seller in the Southeast, Northeast, Northwest, Central, and Southwest Power Pool regions, as defined by 18 C.F.R. 35.36(a). 9. Effective Date. This Tariff is effective on the date specified by the Commission. This Tariff shall continue in effect until terminated or changed in accordance with any applicable regulatory requirements.

The Parties acknowledge and agree that Westwing I shall be the sole Party with title to the Shared Facilities and shall be entitled to all deductions, credits, and other tax benefits with respect to the Shared Facilities (the “Tax Benefits”). Westwing II shall not take or omit to take any action that results in the disqualification of the Shared Facilities for, or recapture of, all or any portion of the Tax Benefits. 2.2 Lease of Shared Facilities. From the Lease Commencement Date until the twentieth anniversary of the Commercial Operation date of the Westwing II Project (the “Initial Lease Term”) or the earlier termination of this Agreement, Westwing I shall lease to Westwing II an undivided interest equal to Westwing II’s Percentage Interest in the Shared Facilities (the “Undivided Interest”). Westwing II may extend the Lease Term for up to three (3) five-year renewal terms (each, a “Renewal Lease Term”) by providing irrevocable written notice of its election within 90 days from the end of the Initial Lease Term, or the then-current Renewal Lease Term. The Renewal Lease Term commences on the day after the end of the Initial Lease Term or the then-current Renewal Lease Term, as applicable, and ends on the date that is five (5) years thereafter, unless earlier terminated pursuant to the provisions hereof. 2.3 Rent. For and in consideration of the use and possession of the Undivided Interest, Westwing II shall pay Rent to Westwing I on the Lease Commencement Date and in advance on each anniversary of the Lease Commencement Date during the Initial Lease Term. The Parties acknowledge that the Rent amounts in Appendix A represent the Parties’ determination of the Fair Market Rent for the lease of the Undivided Interest during each year of the Initial Lease Term. The Rent payable on the twentieth anniversary of the Lease Commencement Date shall be pro-rated for the remaining Initial Term. If Westwing II duly exercises its option to renew this Agreement under Section 2.2, Westwing II shall pay Rent equal to Fair Market Rent on the first day during the Renewal Lease Term and in advance of each anniversary thereof during the Renewal Lease Term. Westwing II shall pay Rent in United States dollars by wire transfer of immediately available funds prior to 5:00 p.m. Arizona Time on the applicable due date, to an account designated in writing by Westwing I to Westwing II no later than three Business Days prior to the applicable due date. Westwing II’s obligation to pay Rent is absolute and unconditional and is not subject to any abatement, counterclaim, defense, deferment, interruption, recoupment, reduction or setoff for any reason whatsoever; provided, that nothing contained herein impairs Westwing II’s right to maintain an independent action at law or in equity. 2.4 Net Lease; Risk of Loss. Westwing II shall be responsible for its Percentage Interest of all Shared Expenses, as set forth in Section 3 below. Westwing II shall bear all risk of loss, damage, destruction, theft and condemnation to or of the Undivided Interest from any cause whatsoever. Westwing II shall at its expense and risk promptly repair or cause the Undivided Interest to be repaired to a condition acceptable to Westwing I. 2.5 Shared Premises Agreements and Land Matters. 2.5.1 Each of Westwing I and Westwing II shall comply with all the terms and conditions of the Shared Premises Agreements, the Land Matters, and the Governmental Approvals. 2.5.2 Subject to their authority or ability to do so, the Parties shall timely execute the necessary instruments to ensure each Owner has sufficient rights to use the applicable Shared Premises on which the Shared Facilities are located. Manager will add such instruments to the Shared Premises Agreements and the Parties shall cooperate to update Exhibit B of this Agreement to include any such additional instruments, amendments, or assignments. 2.5.3 Any amounts due under the terms of the Shared Premises Agreements shall be paid by the Manager, subject to reimbursement by the Owners in accordance with Section 3. 2.5.4 No Shared Premises Agreement may be terminated, modified, or amended without the consent of all of the Owners that are party to, or that directly enjoy rights or benefits under, such Shared Premises Agreement. Nevertheless, if an Owner wishes to terminate its interest in a Shared Premises Agreement, and such termination (i) is permitted by the Shared Premises Agreement itself or by the counterparty thereto and (ii) will have no adverse effect on any other Owner thereto, then such Owner may terminate its interest in that Shared Premises Agreement. The permitted termination by an Owner of its interest in a Shared Premises Agreement shall not cause or be deemed to cause the release of such Owner for any Liabilities or obligations accruing prior to such termination. 2.6 Access to Shared Facilities. Subject to Section 2.5, each Owner and its Representatives shall have non-exclusive access to the Shared Facilities (a) for inspection of the Shared Facilities, (b) for any required maintenance of the Shared Facilities agreed to be undertaken by the Owners or not performed by the Manager in accordance with Section 7, (c) for the installation, maintenance, or repairs of the Shared Facilities or Project Specific Assets, and (d) for the operation of the Shared Facilities, all in accordance with this Agreement. Notwithstanding the foregoing, except in the event of an Emergency, each Owner shall provide no less than twenty-four (24) hours’ prior notice to Manager and the other Owners of its intent to access the Shared Facilities, and no less than forty-eight (48) hours’ prior notice to Manager and the other Owners prior to performing any maintenance or repairs pursuant to clause (b) or (c) above. The Manager, an Owner and/or any Owner’s Representatives shall follow all applicable safety, security and site rules established by the agreement of the Owners and Manager, and shall comply with all applicable Shared Premises Agreements, Land Matters, Laws, and Governmental Approvals when on the Shared Premises or accessing the Shared Facilities, except to the extent that following any such rule would violate applicable Law. In the event of an Emergency, prior notice is not required to access the Shared Facilities to respond to the Emergency, but the Owner shall provide notice of access to Manager and all Owners as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter (no more than twenty-four (24) hours after access). 2.7 No Interference, Cooperation and Over-Burdening. An Owner’s use of the Shared Assets or the operation of its Project may not interfere with the use and enjoyment by any other Owner of its rights in such Shared Assets or the operation of its Project, except as specifically provided herein. Subject to the terms and conditions of this Agreement, including Section 5.13, each of the Owners shall cooperate in good faith to accommodate each of the other Owners’ use of the Shared Assets for the benefit of the Projects as contemplated by this Agreement. Each Owner acknowledges and agrees that the use of the Shared Assets by the Projects as contemplated herein does not, separately or in the aggregate, constitute an overburdening of the Shared Assets, or any part thereof. No Owner will use or permit the use of the Shared Assets in any manner that would create waste or nuisance, or that would jeopardize the issuance or maintenance of any insurance policy relating to the Shared Assets or Project Specific Assets or any Governmental Approval as to the Shared Assets or any Project Specific Assets, nor otherwise conduct or cause to be conducted operations on its Project Site or on the Shared Premises that would have similar effects on, or otherwise damage or interfere with, the Shared Assets. 2.8 Additional Real Property Rights and Facilities. 2.8.1 To the extent that any additional real property and rights therein (“Additional Shared Premises”) or physical facilities (“Additional Shared Facilities,” and together with the Additional Shared Premises, the “Additional Shared Assets”) that relate to the Shared Assets or operation thereof, are required by any Owner (to reach Commercial Operation of a Project, continue operating a Project or repower a Project), such Owner or the Manager may give written notice to the other Owners, of such requirement, with a reasonable explanation of why such Additional Shared Assets are needed. The Owners receiving such notice shall have thirty (30) days after receiving such notice to determine if such Additional Shared Assets are also needed for its Project and to so notify the other Owners and Manager in writing of its election or rejection to participate in the acquisition, installation, and/or construction of such Additional Shared Assets. An Owner’s failure to notify the other Owners and Manager of its election or rejection to participate within such thirty (30) day period will be deemed a rejection of the addition of the proposed Additional Shared Assets. Any Additional Shared Assets that the Owners agree to add (as Shared Assets to be governed by this Agreement) shall be (a) procured jointly by the Owners, (b) added to the Shared Premises and/or Shared Facilities, as applicable, under this Agreement, and (c) held in undivided ownership interests by the Owners in an amount equal to their Percentage Interests. If one or more of the other Owners do not agree to add Additional Shared Assets requested by an Owner or the Manager under this Section 2.8.1, then nothing herein shall prevent the requesting Owner from acquiring the additional premises or facilities needed by and to be held by such Owner, not as part of the Shared Assets hereunder, and not subject to the terms of this Agreement, provided that any additional facilities so acquired shall not, in the reasonable judgment of both Manager and the other Owners, interfere with the development, construction, operation, usage or the maintenance of the Shared Assets or the other Projects, or otherwise violate the terms and conditions of this Agreement, the Land Matters, Governmental Approvals or applicable Laws. Nothing contained herein shall require an Owner to reimburse another Owner for any Additional Shared Assets unless it has expressly agreed to do so in writing. 2.8.2 Except as otherwise provided in this Agreement, no Owner shall construct, install or place any additional facilities on the Shared Premises. 2.9 Conditions to Installation of Additional Shared Facilities or Connecting Projects to the Shared Facilities. Any Owner installing Additional Shared Facilities or connecting its Project to the Shared Facilities shall (a) not interfere with the use or access by the other Owners of the Shared Facilities, except as may be necessary during the installation, repair, or replacement of Shared Facilities, (b) to the extent commercially reasonable, schedule during an off-peak period any required disconnection of the Shared Facilities to conduct construction activities to minimize the impact on the Projects of the other Owners, (c) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice of commencement of such construction activities together with a reasonably detailed description thereof, (d) provide at least thirty (30) days’ prior written notice of any planned outages, and the durations thereof, of the Shared Facilities that would result in a disconnection of the other Owners’ Projects, (e) take into consideration, to the extent commercially reasonable, any changes in the construction plans or timing of construction required or requested by another Owner, provided, that such other Owner does not attempt to interfere with the installation of the proposed Additional Shared Facilities or connection of a Project, unless such installation can reasonably be expected to result in an Emergency or violate the terms of the Shared Premises Agreements, the Land Matters, Governmental Approvals, or this Agreement, (f) be responsible for obtaining and complying with any necessary Governmental Approvals and providing documentary evidence of such Governmental Approvals to the Owners and Manager, and (g) compensate the other Owners’ Projects for all lost revenues as a result of lost or reduced generation due to an outage, reduced use or disconnection of another Owner’s Project. Any Owner (i) installing Additional Shared Facilities that are not needed by, rejected by, or would not, as reasonably determined by such affected Owner, benefit any other Owner, or (ii) connecting its own Project to the Shared Facilities, shall indemnify, defend and hold harmless the other Owners from all Liabilities, including third party claims, property and revenue losses incurred, as a result of such construction or installation activities, but such installing Owner may seek reimbursement for such indemnified costs from insurance required by Section 11 to the extent such insurance provides coverage for such indemnified costs. Installation of Additional Shared Facilities that are expressly consented to by such Owners, shall be installed jointly by the Owners or by the Manager at the direction of the Owners and will be at the risk of all the Owners, and each Owner shall have the right to review and approve all design, planning and installation elements in connection with such installation, and will bear any risk of loss thereof in proportion with its Percentage Interest in the Additional Shared Facilities, to the extent such loss is not covered by the insurance required by Section 11. 3. SHARED EXPENSES 3.1 Liabilities for the Account of the Owners; No Charging of Fees, Premiums or Profits. Except as specifically set forth in this Agreement, each Party shall be solely responsible for its Liabilities relating to its Project and Project Specific Assets, including without limitation, all Liabilities arising from acquiring, designing, installing, constructing, using, operating, maintaining and repairing its Project Specific Assets. Each Party shall, at its sole cost and expense, maintain in good working order and repair at all times each part of its Project that connects with, will connect with, or affects the Shared Facilities or the Shared Premises. Each Owner (or Owners, if any Additional Shared Assets are being acquired or installed at the joint expense of two or more Owners) acquiring or installing any Additional Shared Assets shall be responsible for, and pay, all Liabilities relating to the acquisition or installation, as applicable, of the Additional Shared Assets, except to the extent otherwise provided in Section 2.9. Further, each Party shall be responsible for all Liabilities arising from such Party’s actions or inactions in violation of this Agreement, the Shared Premises Agreements, Land Matters, and Governmental Approvals. The Parties agree that the purpose of this Agreement is for the Parties and their respective Projects to benefit from the cost savings, convenience and efficiencies that result from the sharing of the Shared Assets, and no Party shall charge any other Party any fee, premium or other profit relating to the Shared Assets or services provided under this Agreement, other than the Rent in respect of the Undivided Interest. 3.2 Shared Expenses. 3.2.1 Each Owner shall be responsible for and shall reimburse the Manager (in accordance with Section 3.3) for Liabilities arising under or relating to the following (collectively, the “Shared Expenses”) according to its respective Percentage Interest in the Shared Facilities: (a) the Liabilities arising under each Shared Premises Agreement, and the use, maintenance, repair, and inspection of the applicable portion of the Shared Premises; (b) subject to Section 3.2.3, any fees, expenses or liabilities incurred by or otherwise allocable to Manager hereunder (including the use, maintenance, operation, repair, and inspection of the Shared Premises); (c) an Owner’s responsibility for the use, maintenance, operation, repair, and inspection of the Shared Facilities, including any Liabilities under the HV O M Agreement and those Shared Facilities expenses that may be incurred prior to connecting such Owner’s Project to the Shared Facilities; and (d) the Liabilities arising under the Interconnection Agreement, including any fees or expenses for use, maintenance, operation repair, and inspection thereof. 3.2.2 Each Owner may, from time to time, propose additional categories or types of expenses to be Shared Expenses to be administered jointly by the Owners, or by the Manager at the direction of the Owners in accordance with this Section 3.2. Any such proposed expense must be approved by all of the Owners. 3.2.3 Notwithstanding the foregoing, none of the following shall constitute Shared Expenses: (a) the cost of developing and constructing the Shared Facilities, including without limitation, development, permitting, initial procurement, construction, installation, financing and any other costs incurred in connection with the Shared Facilities of any Project prior to sharing the use thereof in accordance with this Agreement; or (b) the cost and expense of any Project Specific Assets and the connection and integration of Project Specific Assets with any Shared Facilities (including without limitation, any design, procurement, construction, or installation costs). 3.3 Invoicing; Late Payments. No later than ten (10) days after the end of each calendar month following the Effective Date, the Manager shall invoice the Owners for their respective portions of the Shared Expenses. Manager’s invoice shall include a detailed breakdown of the Shared Expenses and each Owner’s share of the Shared Expenses, along with wire transfer instructions for making payment to Manager. Each Owner shall make all payments to Manager (or directly to the other Owners to whom the Shared Expenses may be payable) under this Section 3.3 by wire transfer of immediately available funds as provided in the Manager’s invoice, within thirty (30) days of receipt of such invoice. All sums not paid within thirty (30) days after receipt of Manager’s invoice shall thereafter bear interest at the Default Rate. Each Owner will have the right to audit, and receive supporting documentation for, any expenses or other amounts required to be paid by such Owner under this Agreement. If there is a dispute as to any amount invoiced by Manager, the Owners shall pay all amounts not in dispute in accordance with this Section 3.3. The Owners shall pay any disputed amount ultimately determined as payable with interest thereon at the Default Rate accruing from the date of receipt of the Manager’s disputed invoice. 4. USE OF SHARED ASSETS 4.1 Use by Projects. Subject to the other requirements of this Agreement, each Owner shall have the non-exclusive right to use the Shared Electrical Facilities to the extent of its Percentage Interest therein, as set forth in Exhibit C attached hereto. The foregoing use rights include non-exclusive use of the capacity of the Shared Electrical Facilities to collect, transmit, aggregate, transform, control, shape or otherwise regulate and/or carry electrical energy in an amount in proportion to such Owner’s relative Percentage Interest. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement, each Owner separately owns and shall own the electrical energy generated by its Project. Each Owner shall have the non-exclusive right to use the Retention Basin (as described in Exhibit C) for the collection of stormwater runoff from such Owner’s Project Site. 4.2 Metering/Line Losses. As required by the Interconnection Agreement and Section 5.4 below, each Owner shall each arrange for metering of its Project, including those adjustments that are necessary to account for losses occurring between each Project’s meter and the Point of Interconnection. 4.3 Curtailment. The Manager shall, and each applicable Owner shall cooperate to promptly interrupt, reduce or curtail deliveries of energy to or on the Shared Electrical Facilities (a) when necessary in order to maintain or repair any part of the Shared Electrical Facilities in accordance with Section 7.2.1 and Exhibit E, (b) if interruption, reduction or curtailment is necessary for safety or Emergencies or the energy delivered to, or transmitting on, the Shared Facilities jeopardizes the integrity or use of the Shared Electrical Facilities, (c) if required pursuant to, or to comply with the Interconnection Provider’s tariff(s), (d) if it is otherwise required to do so in accordance with any applicable requirements of NERC or any successor organization certified by FERC to propose and enforce mandatory standards for the reliable operation and planning of the bulk power system throughout the United States of America, and (e) as otherwise agreed by the Owners. With respect to an interruption, reduction or curtailment of deliveries of energy pursuant to clauses (a)-(d) of the immediately preceding sentence, the Manager shall limit the length of such interruption, reduction or curtailment to that time reasonably necessary to address the event or circumstance resulting in such interruption, reduction or curtailment, or otherwise to comply with the Interconnection Provider’s tariff. If an Owner fails to promptly comply with this Section 4.3 (other than pursuant to clause (e)), the Manager may effectuate the same by direct action. 4.4 Allocation. If and to the extent that any interruption, reduction, or curtailment pursuant to Section 4.3 is caused by or otherwise can be attributed to an individual Project or two individual Projects, then the Manager shall limit the direction to interrupt, reduce, or curtail to the applicable Project or Projects, pro rata according to fault as reasonably determined by the Manager. If and to the extent that any interruption, reduction, or curtailment pursuant to Section 4.3 cannot be attributed to one specific Project or two Projects, then for each hour the interruption, reduction, or curtailment shall be allocated to each Project based on the Percentage Interests. 4.5 Shared Facilities Representatives. On or promptly following the date of Commercial Operation of an Owner’s Project, such Owner shall, by written notice to the other Owners and Manager, designate an individual (the “Shared Facilities Representative”), who will have authority to bind the Owner in all matters concerning this Agreement (other than to amend this Agreement), to communicate on a day-to-day basis with the other Owners and to direct Manager regarding operational and maintenance issues. Each Owner may change its Shared Facilities Representative at any time and from time to time by prior written notice to the other Owners and Manager. 4.6 Liens. Westwing II shall not directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities, including but not limited to Taxes (other than for Taxes not yet due), judgments, construction work, repair and restoration, or materials furnished, other than, from and after the Lease Commencement Date, its leasehold interest in the Undivided Interest. From and after the Lease Commencement Date, Westwing I shall not directly or indirectly, create, incur, or permit to exist any lien on the Shared Facilities, including but not limited to Taxes (other than for Taxes not yet due), judgments, construction work, repair and restoration, or materials furnished, which are not subject to the lease of the Undivided Interest pursuant to Article 2. Except as provided in Section 15.2, no Owner will create, permit or suffer to exist by, through or under such Owner or such Owner’s Representatives, and hereby waives for itself and its Representatives, any Liens on the Shared Premises or Project Specific Assets of the other Owners, including (a) Liens for Taxes, unless such Liens only are not yet delinquent or are being contested in good faith by appropriate proceedings, and (b) Liens in favor of carriers’, warehouseman’s, mechanics’, materialmen’s, repairmen’s or other like Liens, unless such Liens only arise in the ordinary course of business of such Owner and for amounts that are not yet due or which are being contested in good faith by appropriate proceedings; provided, in the case of any such permitted Lien in clauses (a) and (b) above, so long as any such proceeding does not involve any substantial danger of the sale, forfeiture or loss of any part of the Shared Premises or any other Owner’s Project Specific Assets and such Owner posts any bond that is required by applicable Law to avoid such sale, forfeiture or loss while such claims are being contested. Each Owner will take prompt steps to discharge or obtain a release bond under applicable Law for any unpermitted Lien filed against any such Shared Premises or Project Specific Assets of the other Owners. If any Owner creating a Lien prohibited hereby fails to discharge or obtain a release bond under applicable law promptly for any such prohibited Lien, each other Owner shall have the right to notify the Owner which created the prohibited Lien in writing and to take any reasonable action to satisfy, defend, settle or otherwise remove the Lien at such breaching Owner’s expense. An Owner’s rights to pursue remedies at law or equity for a breach of this Agreement by any other Owner shall not be limited by this Section 4.6, and may include seeking and placing judgment Liens and exercising on the same to the extent otherwise permitted at Law and this Agreement. 5. OBLIGATIONS AND CERTAIN RIGHTS OF THE OWNERS 5.1 Standards of Performance; Action, Omission or Failure to Perform an Obligation That Results in a Material Adverse Effect on Another Owner or That Owner’s Project. Notwithstanding any other provision of this Agreement to the contrary, each Owner will develop, construct, operate and maintain its Project and perform its obligations under this Agreement in accordance with (a) all applicable Laws, (b) Prudent Industry Practices, (c) the Interconnection Agreement and the applicable terms of the Shared Premises Agreements, (d) any and all Governmental Approvals, (e) all applicable Land Matters, and (f) the applicable power purchase agreement of each respective Owner, as applicable. No Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) will take any action, omit to take any action or fail to perform any obligation under this Agreement, the Shared Premises Agreements, the Interconnection Agreement, Governmental Approvals, Land Matters, or power purchase agreements, that materially and adversely affects another Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) or another Owner’s (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) Project or gives rise to a Liability affecting another Owner (and prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II), such other Owner’s (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) Projects, or the Shared Assets, including any action, omission or failure to perform an obligation that results in damage to, disconnection of, or an outage of another Owner’s (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) Projects. 5.2 Taxes. Unless otherwise directed by the Owners, the Manager shall pay all real and personal property Taxes, general or special, levied against the Shared Assets before delinquency and before any fine, interest or penalty will become due or be imposed for their non-payment, except that the Manager may withhold payment of any Tax if Manager is contesting the payment of such Tax in good faith by appropriate proceedings and such proceeding does not involve any danger of the sale, forfeiture or loss of any part of such Shared Asset, whether or not the posting of any bond is required by applicable Law to avoid such sale, forfeiture or loss while the payment of such Tax is being contested, and notifies all the Owners thereof in writing at least thirty (30) days before the original due date for payment of the applicable amount. All such Taxes and assessments paid by the Manager shall be treated as Shared Expenses and invoiced to the Owners in accordance with Section 3.3. 5.3 Environmental Compliance. Each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) shall, with respect to its Project (including its Project Specific Assets, and the Project Site upon which its Project is installed), be responsible for and shall have exclusive control (as between the Parties) over all investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action required by (i) any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters, or (ii) any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to such Owner’s (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) use, operation or ownership of its Project (including its Project Specific Assets and Project Site). The Manager shall, with respect to the Shared Premises and the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Premises, subject to the oversight and direction of the Owners, oversee all investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action required by any Governmental Authority now or hereafter authorized to regulate environmental or other matters or by any consent decree or court or administrative order now or hereafter applicable to the Owners’ use, operation or ownership of the Shared Premises or the Shared Facilities located on the Shared Premises, and subject to Sections 10.1 and 10.2, each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) shall be responsible, in proportion to its relative Percentage Interest, for all Liabilities related to such investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action. Manager shall keep all Owners fully appraised as to the above matters affecting the Shared Premises and shall consult with all of them prior to taking any action involving any Governmental Authority or risk of incurring any Liability. The Owners shall manage and control all investigations and any environmental cleanup, remediation or related activities with respect to the Shared Premises, or direct Manager to do so. Each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) shall be responsible, in proportion to its relative Percentage Interest, for all Liabilities related to investigations, studies, cleanup, corrective action or response, or remedial action with respect to the Shared Premises, and the Owners shall mutually agree with respect to the management and control of all investigations and any environmental cleanup, remediation or related activities with respect to the Shared Premises, or shall direct Manager to do so. 5.4 Interconnection. The Interconnection Agreement shall be held and used solely to permit the interconnection of electricity generated by or on behalf of the Projects owned by the Owner (or such Owner’s successors or assigns). Each Owner shall have an undivided ownership interest in the Interconnection Agreement and possess an undivided right to enjoy all of such interest as an “Interconnection Customer” thereunder. Each of Westwing I and Westwing II agrees and acknowledges that, for purposes of the Interconnection Agreement, (i) neither such Party has an expectation that either will be treated other than as a single entity, i.e. that “Interconnection Customer,” under the Interconnection Agreement and that the performance of the “Interconnection Customer’s” obligations under the Interconnection Agreement may be not excused by any reason of the failure of either Westwing I or Westwing II to agree with respect to any obligation of the “Interconnection Customer” thereunder and (ii) this Agreement shall constitute the “Common Tenants Agreement” under and as defined in the Interconnection Agreement. For the avoidance of doubt, each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) will make all diligent efforts to separately deliver and meter the electrical energy generated by its Project. 5.5 Meteorological and Operational Data. All Owners shall make all meteorological and operational data available to Manager upon request. In addition, to the extent required to comply with Governmental Approvals or Laws, each Owner shall share meteorological and operational data regarding its respective Project and the Shared Facilities with the Manager (but not the other Owners), with the mutual objective of optimizing the operational and maintenance efficiency of each of the Projects and the Shared Facilities. The sharing Owner makes no representation or warranty, express or implied, and will have no Liability with respect to the data so provided, whether for completeness, accuracy or otherwise. The Receiving Party will maintain the confidentiality of the data received in accordance with the requirements of this Agreement. 5.6 Voting or Approval Rights. Unless specifically provided in this Agreement, each Owner shall have the right to vote or give its approval on any matter requiring or needing a vote or approval of the Owners. Unless otherwise specified herein, a unanimous vote of the Owners shall be required for any approval to be provided by the Owners hereunder. 5.7 Relationship of the Owners. The rights, duties, obligations and Liabilities of the Owners (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) under this Agreement will be individual and not joint or collective, and no Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) shall be responsible for the default of another Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) under this Agreement. It is not the intention of the Owners (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) to create, nor will this Agreement be deemed to create, any tenancy-in-common, partnership, agency, joint venture, trust, or association of profit, or to authorize any Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) to act as an agent, servant or employee for another Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II). The Owners intended for the lease of the Undivided Interest to be treated for income tax purposes as a “true lease” by the Westwing I Project Company of Westwing II’s Percentage Interest in the Shared Facilities and not a transfer of ownership of such assets. Each Owner shall report the income Tax consequences of the lease of the Undivided Interest in a manner consistent with this Section 5.7. If requested by an Owner, the Owners shall make an election under Section 761 of the Code not to be treated as a partnership for purposes of subchapter K of the Code. Each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) will remain solely responsible for the actions of its own employees. 5.8 Regulatory Status. Each Owner operating a Project represents and warrants that it is an EWG, and such Owner covenants to maintain its status as an EWG for so long as it is a Party to this Agreement or have any interest in the Shared Assets that requires it to be an EWG. No Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) will take any action that could adversely impact another Owner’s ability to qualify as an EWG. 5.9 No Dedication of Property; No Public Access. Each Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) agrees that entering into this Agreement, performing its obligations hereunder, or exercising its rights hereunder, either in whole or part, is not intended to be, and shall in no way be construed as or deemed to be, a dedication to public or quasi-public use or purpose of any of the Project Specific Assets of any Owner (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II), any Shared Assets, or any portion of the foregoing. The Owners (and, prior to becoming an Owner, Westwing II) also agree that, unless so ordered by a Governmental Authority, there shall be no, and none of them shall provide, public access to the Shared Assets or any portion of them, provided, however, that each Owner shall permit access to the Shared Assets to the extent necessary to permit an Offtaker to inspect the Project Specific Assets associated with the Project from which the Offtaker is purchasing energy, capacity, or ancillary services provided that such inspection shall not unreasonably interfere with the operation and maintenance of the Shared Assets, and any Offtaker accessing the Shared Assets to inspect the Project Specific Assets shall abide by any and all reasonable safety rules and procedures established by Manager that are not inconsistent with this Agreement or otherwise applicable to the Shared Assets, as communicated to them in writing by the Manager prior to their access to the Shared Assets. The Owners undertake to cooperate in enforcing such requirement for limiting access to the Shared Assets, including establishing and enforcing procedures and protocol for security, safety, and protection of the Shared Assets. To the extent any Governmental Authority attempts to compel the Owners to provide public access to or use of the Shared Assets, the Owners shall cooperate to dispute and resist such compulsion by any and all judicial, administrative, legislative, political and other legal means available, unless all of the Owners agree otherwise and no Owner’s Project is materially adversely affected thereby. Notwithstanding the foregoing, the Owners shall comply with any Governmental Approvals’ requirements. Additionally, to the extent any Owner Project’s Governmental Approvals are expressly conditioned on providing a third party access to cross over the Shared Premises, such rights of access do not adversely impact the development, construction, operation, maintenance or repair of the Shared Facilities, any Project, or any part thereof, as confirmed by an Independent Engineer, and provided that no public right of access may be created in any Shared Facilities, all of which are the property of and allocated to the Owners and their Projects, the Owners shall cooperate in good faith and negotiate a resolution of such request to facilitate the Governmental Approvals. 5.10 Crossing and Co-location Rights. Each Owner hereunder shall be permitted to cross and encroach upon the Shared Premises with its Project Specific Assets (including collection, communication and fiber lines, gas and water pipes, utility services, and access roads) solely to the extent necessary to develop, construct, operate and maintain its Project, provided that any such crossings, encroachments, or overhang shall be subject to the noninterference and overburdening protections of Section 2.7 above.
